In this category, we will attempt to categorize commons infrastructures following the [[NORA Commons Resource Model]] (Needs, Organisational Forms, Resources for Abundance), suggested by Wolfgang Hoeschele and the [[Commons Abundance Network]].

See:

# [[Commons-Based Needs]]
# [[Commons-Based Organizational Forms]]
# [[Commons-Based Resources]]

We are initially focusing on material needs.

Please read:

* [[Kevin Jones on the Turn to Commons-Based Property]] : This text is written in the context of Neighborhood Economics and the author Kevin Jones calls it the collective turn. But what he describes is a turn towards common stewardship and even property models.


==Categorising Needs==

See: [[Commons-Based Needs]]

Please note that Carl Mallman's earlier work inspired Max-Neef and that Roberto Verzola expanded on this work by clarifying the concepts of scarcity and abundance:

* [[Well-Being System of Carlos Mallman and the Bariloche Foundation]]

* [[Roberto Verzola on the Commons-Oriented Economics of Abundance]]

We also recommend checking our own: [[Introduction to Commons Economics]]

